At least six people have beenÂ killed after a 21-storey buidling under construction collapsed in Ikoyi district in Lagos, with dozens feared trapped inside. Emergency services crews and residents are currently at the scene trying to free workers trapped under the rubble of the luxury apartment building, which has been under construction for the past two years. Gbolahan Oki, an official of the Lagos State Building Control Agency, has said that the owner of the building, was given approval to construct only 15 floors. While authorities have said it is unclear what caused this building collapse, it is a common occurence in Lagos and elsewhere in Nigeria. In previous cases, the use of substandard building materials, the deployment of unsafe, cost-cutting techniques in housing construction, and the lack of professional supervision at various levels of the construction process.